        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/da6949/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-03T15:22:44.850Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>My Idea:</strong></p>\n<p>Add a subtle but clear visual indicator on the main chat list when a contact has posted a story, without requiring the user to enter the chat thread or head to the stories tab.</p>\n<p><strong>Problem:</strong></p>\n<p>Right now it‚Äôs too easy to miss stories unless you open each chat. The story tab is rarely opened by my contacts as it‚Äôs not very in your face and I appreciate the idea behind that. However I don‚Äôt think showing a subtle cue for people you‚Äôve started conversations with goes against Signal‚Äôs philosophy.</p>\n<p>If needed, make it a setting people can turn off.</p>\n<p>This would make stories more useful and easier to keep up with, without adding any new notifications or clutter.</p>\n<p><strong>Proposed Solution:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Display a non-intrusive visual cue (eg a ring or dot) next to the contacts avatar on the main chat list when a new story is available.</li>\n<li>Only show indicators for contacts the user has had recent conversations with (say the last 30 days).</li>\n<li>Optional setting to disable story indicators entirely - for those who prefer no visual cues.</li>\n</ul>",
