        "id": 272996,
        "name": null,
        "username": "signaluser314",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/ed8c4c/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-04T03:21:40.819Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I think you‚Äôve hit the nail on the head here. Currently, visual signals for new Stories are too subtle and don‚Äôt have a lot of value as currently designed.</p>\n<p>The average user in Signal largely spends their time on the Chats tab and that‚Äôs all they focus on because it brings immediate, obvious, and clear value. Stories don‚Äôt get the same level of treatment.</p>\n<p>I know they‚Äôre trying to avoid a ‚Äúsocial media‚Äù-esque form of communication, but combining the 24 hour timer with poor visual feedback to explain to the user that there‚Äôs something to view means that Stories are missed, thus people don‚Äôt send them, thus no one uses the feature.</p>\n<p>I think Stories do have value without falling into ‚Äúsocial media schlock‚Äù, but it feels like there has been no obvious push to try to improve their usability from when they were first implemented.</p>\n<p>Anything to make then not easily missable seems like a step in the right direction, especially since users who dislike them can always turn them off.</p>",
