        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rubcap/{size}/52443_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-14T09:46:57.208Z",
        "cooked": "<p>+1 for improving the visibility of new stories, especially those coming from close contacts.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"signaluser314\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"70820\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/ed8c4c/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> signaluser314:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The average user in Signal largely spends their time on the Chats tab</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Exactly. Many of my friends and relatives just don‚Äôt notice that stories were posted.</p>\n<p>I see Stories in Signal as a decent alternative for Facebook, Instagram and the like. It allows me to share a picture or event with family and close friends. But when stories aren‚Äôt read <em>at all</em>, there is no purpose for this feature in Signal.</p>\n<p>Signal developers, please prioritize a solution for this!</p>",
